title: Determine the Domain
text: The values of $$x$$ that can be taken are integers from $$-3$$ to $$3$$. The lowest $$x$$ value point is $$(-3,9)$$ and highest $$x$$ value point is $$(3,9)$$.

title: Determine the Range
text: The values of $$y$$ that can be taken are integers from $$0$$ to $$9$$. The lowest $$y$$ value point being $$(0,0)$$ and the highest $$y$$ value point being $$(-3,9)$$ or $$(3,9)$$.

title: One to One Functions
text: Is $$x$$ and $$y$$ one to one? Recall that a one to one function is a function in which each input value is mapped to one unique output value.
